download visual studio and mingw
    -https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/cpp/config-mingw
    (write vs code with mingw)on google
    -visual code
        -c/cpp extension
    -set bin folder of mingw path after downloading it
-open VS code- "code . or code" in cmd
-download mingw uing above link
-"pacman -Syu" in cmd to update to latest version of mingw
-"pacman -Su" command in MSYS2 app
-install some tools and the mingw-w64 GCC to start compiling
    -"pacman -S --needed base-devel mingw-w64-x86_64-toolchain" in cmd
    -now set path to C:\msys64\mingw64\bin in environment variables

compile and run
-cd.. previous folder
- mkdir to create folder, del to delete file,
- to compile code -> g++ "file name".C
- executable file will be created write its name to run it
- #include<bits/stdc++.h> add many header
-g++ helloworld.cpp -o hello to create executable file named hello other then just a.

github
-download git windows install
    -unclear use git from bash only if is marked while installation
    -git init to initialise repository
    -git add . to create a checkpoint
    -git commit -m" message like its initialized"
    -git remote add origin https://github.com/nakul498/cppwork.git
    -git push -u origin master

additional
